The course is conducted as a series of special seminars devotedto various theoretical issues arising in private law.  During the first yearof the doctoral program, each doctoral candidate is required to present an original research papers and to serve as principal examiner for another paper.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to enhance the knowledge base of doctoral candidates in fundamental issues arising in private law, primarily through the independent research of their doctoral thesis and series of seminars.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The course is intended to improve the knowledge base of doctoral students regarding selected specialties of civil law, primarily through the presentation and discussion of topical papers prepared by the students and derived from research conducted for their doctoral dissertations.
